Here’s a minimalist, modern, and responsive webpage code for your personal blog, including HTML, CSS, and JavaScript for a contact form:

### HTML (index.html)
```html
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>My Personal Blog</title>
    <link rel="stylesheet" type="text/css" href="styles.css">
</head>
<body>
    <header>
        <h1>Welcome to My Blog</h1>
        <nav>
            <ul>
                <li><a href="#about">About</a></li>
                <li><a href="#posts">Posts</a></li>
                <li><a href="#contact">Contact</a></li>
            </ul>
        </nav>
    </header>
    <section id="about">
        <h2>About Me</h2>
        <p>This is a brief introduction about myself.</p>
    </section>
    <section id="posts">
        <h2>Recent Posts</h2>
        <article>
            <h3>Post Title 1</h3>
            <p>This is a summary of my first post.</p>
        </article>
        <article>
            <h3>Post Title 2</h3>
            <p>This is a summary of my second post.</p>
        </article>
    </section>
    <section id="contact">
        <h2>Contact Me</h2>
        <form id="contactForm">
            <label for="name">Name:</label>
            <input type="text" id="name" name="name" required>
            <label for="email">Email:</label>
            <input type="email" id="email" name="email" required>
            <label for="message">Message:</label>
            <textarea id="message" name="message" required></textarea>
            <button type="submit">Send</button>
        </form>
    </section>
    <footer>
        <p>&copy; 2023 My Personal Blog</p>
    </footer>
    <script src="script.js"></script>
</body>
</html>
